Package: hostapd-s1g
Architecture: any
Depends:
 ${shlibs:Depends},
 ${misc:Depends},
Description: IEEE 802.11 AP daemon with Morse Micro S1G (Wi-Fi HaLow) support
 hostapd-s1g is an IEEE 802.11 access point and IEEE 802.1X/WPA/WPA2/EAP
 authenticator built from the Morse Micro fork of hostap with 802.11ah
 (Wi-Fi HaLow / Sub-1 GHz) support enabled.
 .
 Binaries are installed as hostapd_s1g and hostapd_cli_s1g to allow
 coexistence with the standard Debian hostapd package.

Package: wpa-supplicant-s1g
Architecture: any
Depends:
 ${shlibs:Depends},
 ${misc:Depends},
Description: WPA supplicant with Morse Micro S1G (Wi-Fi HaLow) support
 wpa-supplicant-s1g is a WPA/WPA2/IEEE 802.1X supplicant built from the
 Morse Micro fork of hostap with 802.11ah (Wi-Fi HaLow / Sub-1 GHz)
 support enabled. Includes TWT, standby mode, and keep-alive offload
 features for S1G power management.
 .
 Binaries are installed as wpa_supplicant_s1g, wpa_cli_s1g, and
 wpa_passphrase_s1g to allow coexistence with the standard Debian
 wpasupplicant package.
